downloadDescription: This performance lab created by the Microsoft Project Server engineering team examines a “large” synthetic dataset in response to several common workloads.
detailsSection: This performance lab created by the Microsoft Project Server engineering team explores the behavior of a “large” synthetic dataset in response to several common workloads. You can use this information to provide a rough baseline for Project Server 2013 performance in this defined lab environment.  It is important to note that your actual performance may differ due to numerous variables in your own environment.
installInstructionSection:
1. Click the Download button in the upper right corner of this page to start the download.
  2. Click Save or Save this program to disk.
  3. Find the file on your hard disk and double-click it to open it.
